<% include ../_partials/template/_head.ejs %><body> <% include ../_partials/template/_outdated.ejs %><div id="wrapper"><header><% include ../_partials/template/_header.ejs %></header><div class="clearfix mb"></div><div class="wrap mt"><section class="container mb"><div class="row"><div class="col-12 mb"><h1>.:: IN-Mikro 380 ::.</h1></div><div class="col-12 mb"><p class="text-justify">The IN-MIKRO 380 is a high quality active microphone which can be easily connected to your IP Camera. All you need is an IP Camera device which has a built-in audio input. The following models are currently supported: IN-2901, IN-2905 V2 (year of manufacture 2013), IN-2908, IN-5907, IN-4010, IN-4011, IN-5907HD and the new introduced IN-7011HD. Please take notice, that in order to use this microphone with the IN-4010, In-4011, IN-5907HD or the IN-7011HD you will need to use a different Y-cable for 12V power supplies then for the 5V models.</p></div><div class="col-sm-12 col-md-8"><h3 class="text-muted">Your Advantages</h3><ul><li>Background noises will be reduced (in comparison to a simple included mic)</li><li>Clear and pure sound transmission</li><li>Easy connection to your camera through Chinch</li><li>Adjustable sensitivity of the microphone</li></ul><br><h3 class="text-muted">Content of delivery</h3><ul><li>1x Microphone IN-MIKRO 380</li><li>1x Y-cable for 12V IP Cameras</li><li>1x Screws and dowls</li><li>1x User manual</li></ul></div><div class="col-12 col-md-4"><div class="card shadow"> <img class="card-img-top img-fluid" src="/images/Products/IN-Mikro_380_00.jpg" alt="IN-Mikro 300"><div class="card-block"><p class="card-text">The IN-Mikro 380 Microphone for IP Cameras.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-12 mb"><h2>Installation</h2><h3 class="text-muted">How to connect the Microphone with your Camera?</h3><br><p class="text-justify">The IN-Mikro 380 microphone is powered by your camera´s power supply via a Y-cable that is in the scope of the delivery. The wiring has to be according to the sketch below:</p></div><div class="col-12 mb"><div class="card shadow"> <img class="card-img-top img-fluid" src="/images/Products/IN-Mikro_380_04.png" alt="Infrared Light"><div class="card-block"><p class="card-text">You can power the microphone with the power supply from your camera.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-12 mb"><p class="text-justify">And that is how it will look in a less abstract way:</p></div><div class="col-12 mb"><div class="card shadow"> <img class="card-img-top img-fluid" src="/images/Products/IN-Mikro_380_02.png" alt="Infrared Light"><div class="card-block"><p class="card-text">Take the microphone out of the box...</p></div></div></div><div class="col-12 mb"><div class="card shadow"> <img class="card-img-top img-fluid" src="/images/Products/IN-Mikro_380_03.png" alt="Infrared Light"><div class="card-block"><p class="card-text">...connect it to the Y-cabel that comes with the microphone and use the other two connectors of the cable to make a bridge between the power supply and the camera ...</p></div></div></div><div class="col-12 mb"><div class="card shadow"> <img class="card-img-top img-fluid" src="/images/Products/IN-Mikro_380_01.png" alt="Infrared Light"><div class="card-block"><p class="card-text">...then connect the audio cable of your microphone with your camera´s audio-in. Done!</p></div></div></div></div></section></div><section class="webui mb"><% include ../_partials/content/_webui.ejs %></section><section class="social"><% include ../_partials/content/_social.ejs %></section> <!-- ############################################# Footer ############################################# --><footer><% include ../_partials/template/_footer.ejs %></footer> <% include ../_partials/template/_jsdefaults.ejs %></div></body></html>